---

🔴 1. Main Error (Root Cause)

MountVolume.MountDevice failed:
rpc error: code = Aborted
desc = an operation with the given Volume ID ... already exists

👉 This is a storage (ODF / CSI) stuck operation issue
It means:

Kubernetes tried to attach/mount the PVC

But previous attach/detach operation is stuck

CSI driver thinks operation is still in progress



---

🔴 2. Impact Seen

Pod:

bscf9901-dmp0 → Init:0/1 (stuck)

No IP assigned → volume not mounted → container not starting



---

🟡 3. Node Resource Check

Good news 👇

master1 & master2 → CPU almost 98–101% (critical)

master3 → only 13% CPU (healthy)


👉 So:

Scheduling is OK (pod already on master3)

Problem is NOT CPU

Problem is storage attach



---

🧠 4. Why This Happens (Common in ODF)

Typical reasons:

Node reboot during volume attach

CSI pod restart

Network glitch between node & storage

RBD/CEPH lock not released



---

🔧 5. Step-by-Step Fix

✅ Step 1: Check VolumeAttachment

Run:

oc get volumeattachment | grep 51c66a43

Then describe:

oc describe volumeattachment <name>

👉 If stuck → delete it:

oc delete volumeattachment <name>


---

✅ Step 2: Check if volume attached to wrong node

oc get pvc | grep pvc-e0439e5b
oc describe pvc <pvc-name>

Then:

oc get pv <pv-name> -o yaml

Look for:

nodeAffinity / attachment info


---

✅ Step 3: Restart CSI Pods (VERY IMPORTANT)

Check:

oc get pods -n openshift-storage | grep csi

Restart:

oc delete pod -n openshift-storage -l app=csi-rbdplugin
oc delete pod -n openshift-storage -l app=csi-rbdplugin-provisioner

👉 This clears stuck operations


---

✅ Step 4: Check Ceph Health

oc -n openshift-storage exec -it rook-ceph-tools-... -- ceph -s

Ensure:

HEALTH_OK

If not → storage issue


---

✅ Step 5: Force Pod Restart

oc delete pod bscf9901-dmp0-6fd9b97cc-wl94d


---

🚨 If Still Not Fixed (Advanced)

Check RBD lock manually:

rbd status <image-name> --pool replicapool

Remove lock:

rbd lock remove <image> <lock-id> <locker>


